            <h1 style="color:RGB(52, 183, 235)"><u>VISUAL STUDTIO CODE</u></h1>
            <img src="https://repository-images.githubusercontent.com/657248114/d3c7b91a-b285-4d1e-8429-5de1acc5f61e" width="200" height="100">
        </center>
        <P>Visual Studio is a software development tool created by Microsoft. Think of it like a powerful toolkit that helps programmers write, test, and debug their code. Visual Studio Code (VS Code) is a versatile and widely used source-code editor developed by Microsoft. It’s designed for developers and offers a lightweight yet powerful environment for writing, editing, and debugging code.</P>
        <h2>Features of vs code :</h2>
        <p>1.Code editing:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Syntax Highlighting: Colors your code to make it easier to read.</li>
            <li>Auto-completion: Suggests code completions as you type.</li>
            <li>Code Snippets: Provides templates for common code structures.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>2.Integrated terminal:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Allows you to run command-line tools directly within the editor.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>3.Extensions and Customization:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>You can install extensions to add new features, such as support for different programming languages, themes, and tools.</li>
            <li>Customize the editor’s look and functionality to fit your workflow.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>4.Platform support:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Macos,Widows,Linux.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>5.Debuggig.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Set breakpoints and step through your code to find and fix issues.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>6.File explore: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Browse and manage your project files and folders.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>7.Live share:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Collaborate with others in real-time by sharing your code, terminal, and debugging sessions.</li>
        </ul>
